Dutch salvage firm Smit-Tak said itmay take some three weeks to lift the Swiss tug Orinoko and itslighter Pavo which sank 10 days ago at Karlsruhe in WestGermany, blocking the Rhine river.    Smit-Tak, which with its West German subsidiary HarmsBergung GmbH was commissioned by the local water authorities toraise the vessels, said its lifting fleet was in position anddivers had made the first inspection.    Smit is still preparing its final salvage plan and said thework would begin on Sunday. Reuter&#3;